# Maintain STRUCTURE.md

`STRUCTURE.md` in the project root is a supplementary reference for understanding project layout. It is **not** a replacement for scanning the filesystem — always verify against reality when precision matters.

## Maintenance Rules

- **When adding, deleting, moving, or renaming a file** — update STRUCTURE.md in the same step.
- **At the start of each new task or session** — reconcile STRUCTURE.md against the actual filesystem and fix any drift before proceeding.
- **If you notice a discrepancy** between STRUCTURE.md and the filesystem at any point — trust the filesystem and update the file.

## Content Guidelines

- For each file, include a one-line description of its responsibility — what it does, not just what it is.
- Group files by module/feature area, not just directory nesting.
- Note key architectural decisions and relationships between files (e.g. "X is the only entry point for Y", "A depends on B for config").
- Mark files that are generated or should not be edited manually.
- Keep it concise — if a section grows beyond ~30 entries, summarize subdirectories rather than listing every file.
